Judas's Note:

While the age of the movie isn't much, this has the similar pitfalls of the 300 movie applying tons of grain, blur (It's got the fantasy style glow that results in blacks never being &quot;black&quot;), and other effects to the film post production. In order to obtain the most detail and keep the image as close to that of the original bluray, again no filters are being applied. Any substantial increase in bitrate had no noticeable impact until I hit well over 7500kbps bitrate (which obviously significantly increasing the file size.)
